      <outline text="Emerson Hancock (Seattle, Washington) — Right middle finger contusion; negative X-rays (2026-07-12)" type="link" url="https://www.mlb.com/news/mariners-injuries-and-roster-moves" description="Mariners monitor a rotation piece heading toward the All-Star break"/>
      <outline text="Will Wilson (Seattle, Washington) — Fractured left thumb (2026-07-12)" type="link" url="https://www.mlb.com/news/mariners-injuries-and-roster-moves" description="Mariners' infield depth option now faces a possible lost season"/>
      <outline text="Blaze Alexander (Baltimore, Maryland) — Non-displaced fracture in the left hand after being hit by a pitch from Royals reliever Lucas Erceg, sparking a benches-clearing incident (2026-07-12)" type="link" url="https://www.mlbtraderumors.com/2026/07/orioles-blaze-alexander-suffers-fractured-hand-on-hbp.html" description="Orioles lose a middle infielder for at least a month, with a risk of a season-ending outcome pending further evaluation"/>
      <outline text="Zac Gallen (Phoenix, Arizona) — Right elbow inflammation (2026-07-12)" type="link" url="https://arizonasports.com/mlb/arizona-diamondbacks/zac-gallen-15-day-il-recall-mitch-bratt" description="Diamondbacks lose their staff ace for at least two turns through the rotation"/>
      <outline text="Nick Kurtz (West Sacramento, California (Sutter Health Park; relocating to Las Vegas)) — Right thumb capsule sprain (2026-07-11)" type="link" url="https://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/49334996/athletics-all-star-1b-nick-kurtz-placed-il-thumb-sprain" description="Keeps the 2025 AL Rookie of the Year and scheduled AL All-Star starting first baseman (.266, 20 HR, 66 RBI, MLB-leading 76 walks) out of the July 14 All-Star Game in Philadelphia; catcher Brian Serven recalled from Triple-A in a corresponding move"/>
      <outline text="Nick Lodolo (Cincinnati, Ohio) — Blister on the left index finger (throwing hand); a recurring issue, his fourth stint on the IL for blisters dating back to 2024 (2026-07-11)" type="link" url="https://www.mlbtraderumors.com/2026/07/reds-place-nick-lodolo-on-il-with-blister-recall-chase-petty.html" description="Reds turn to Rhett Lowder to fill Lodolo's rotation spot"/>
      <outline text="Bo Bichette (Queens (Flushing), New York) — General leg soreness and right ankle soreness, aggravated by fouling balls off his legs during a series in Atlanta (2026-07-11)" type="link" url="https://www.bakersfield.com/ap/sports/bo-bichette-held-out-of-mets-lineup-for-second-straight-game-with-leg-soreness/article_c615803d-891c-57fd-87ef-b86becfaf8cc.html" description="Mets manage his workload during a productive stretch (.320 avg, .788 OPS over his last 25 games) heading into the All-Star break"/>
      <outline text="Konnor Griffin (Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania) — Torn tendon (sagittal band) in the left ring finger, sustained diving for a ball; initially placed on the 10-day IL and now transferred to the 60-day IL (2026-07-11)" type="link" url="https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/baseball/news/pirates-konnor-griffin-moved-to-60-day-il/" description="Pirates lose their rookie starting shortstop (the No. 1 overall pick in the 2024 draft) for an extended stretch, his second significant injury of the season after an earlier forearm strain"/>
